\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Running the survey to trace the restore\uc0\u8594 tasks gap.\
Found the gap already \'97 
\f1\fs26 restoreBoard
\f0\fs24  calls 
\f1\fs26 loadBoards()
\f0\fs24  (board 
\f2\b list
\f0\b0  only), never 
\f1\fs26 refreshTasks()
\f0\fs24 . Let me confirm the Trash + Archive handlers and the realtime path to complete the trace.\
Changed nothing \'97 read-only (
\f1\fs26 grep
\f0\fs24 , 
\f1\fs26 Read
\f0\fs24 ). Full trace of why restored boards come back empty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Root cause\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 No restore path ever re-fetches 
\f3\fs26 workspace_tasks
\f2\fs24  into the renderer.
\f0\b0  A board's cards live in WorkspaceContext's 
\f1\fs26 tasks
\f0\fs24  state, which is only ever populated by a 
\f1\fs26 getTasks()
\f0\fs24  call \'97 from the initial load, 
\f1\fs26 refreshTasks()
\f0\fs24 , or 
\f1\fs26 reloadOpenBoard()
\f0\fs24 . Every restore path refreshes the board 
\f2\b list
\f0\b0  but calls none of those, so the restored board renders its columns with zero cards.\
The 
\f1\fs26 tasks
\f0\fs24  state genuinely lacks the board's cards at restore time, by design:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 getTasks
\f2\fs24  excludes archived/trashed boards
\f0\b0  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/main/cloud/boards.ts#L335"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 boards.ts:335}}): it only pulls tasks where the board has 
\f1\fs26 deleted=0 AND archived=0
\f0\fs24 . So while a board sits in Archive/Trash its tasks are (correctly) absent from every 
\f1\fs26 getTasks
\f0\fs24  result.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 deleteBoard
\f2\fs24  also purges them locally
\f0\b0  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/contexts/WorkspaceContext.tsx#L599"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 WorkspaceContext.tsx:599}}): 
\f1\fs26 setTasks(prev => prev.filter(t => t.board_id !== id))
\f0\fs24 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 So on restore, the board becomes eligible again \'97 but only on the 
\f2\b next
\f0\b0  
\f1\fs26 getTasks
\f0\fs24 , which nobody calls.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Each restore path, and what it misses\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 1. 
\f3\fs26 restoreBoard
\f2\fs24  (context)
\f0\b0  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/contexts/WorkspaceContext.tsx#L591"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 WorkspaceContext.tsx:591}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf0 await window.api.boards.restore(id)\
await loadBoards()          // \uc0\u8592  board LIST only\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 loadBoards
\f0\fs24  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/contexts/WorkspaceContext.tsx#L163"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 :163}}) calls just 
\f1\fs26 boards.list
\f0\fs24  + 
\f1\fs26 boards.listArchived
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  
\f1\fs26 setBoards
\f0\fs24 /
\f1\fs26 setArchivedBoards
\f0\fs24 . 
\f2\b No 
\f3\fs26 getTasks
\f2\fs24 /
\f3\fs26 refreshTasks
\f2\fs24 .
\f0\b0  Board reappears in the sidebar, but 
\f1\fs26 boardTasks = tasks.filter(board_id === active)
\f0\fs24  is empty. \uc0\u8592  the core bug.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 2. Archive 
\f3\fs26 handleRestore
\f0\b0\fs24  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/pages/Archive.tsx#L46"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Archive.tsx:46}} \'97 worse, it 
\f2\b bypasses WorkspaceContext entirely
\f0\b0 :\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf0 await window.api.boards.restore(id)\
setBoards(prev => prev.filter(b => b.id !== id))   // Archive's OWN local list\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf0 It never touches the context's board list, tasks, or activeBoard. The restored board won't even show in the sidebar until some other 
\f1\fs26 loadBoards
\f0\fs24  fires (realtime or restart), and its tasks are never loaded.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 3. Trash 
\f3\fs26 handleRestore
\f0\b0\fs24  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/pages/Trash.tsx#L160"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Trash.tsx:160}} \'97 also bypasses the context:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf0 await window.api.boards.undelete(item.item_id)\
await load()                // Trash's OWN list reload\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf0 No context 
\f1\fs26 undeleteBoard
\f0\fs24  exists \'97 it calls the API directly, so the workspace board list and tasks are never refreshed. (Same for 
\f1\fs26 handleRestoreAll
\f0\fs24 .)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 4. Realtime safety net doesn't cover it
\f0\b0  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/contexts/WorkspaceContext.tsx#L378"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 WorkspaceContext.tsx:378}}. A restore mutates 
\f1\fs26 workspace_boards
\f0\fs24 , which echoes over realtime \'97 but:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 scope === 'list'
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  
\f1\fs26 loadBoards()
\f0\fs24  (list only, no tasks).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 scope === 'board'
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  reloads tasks 
\f2\b only if 
\f3\fs26 d.boardId === activeBoardIdRef.current
\f0\b0\fs24  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/src/renderer/src/contexts/WorkspaceContext.tsx#L380"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 :380}}).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 A board-flag change is list-level metadata, and none of the restore handlers switch 
\f1\fs26 activeBoard
\f0\fs24  to the restored board \'97 so the echo lands in the list-only branch and never triggers a 
\f1\fs26 getTasks
\f0\fs24 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Why "manual add / restart" recovers it\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Restart
\f0\b0  is definitive: the mount effect runs a fresh 
\f1\fs26 getTasks()
\f0\fs24 , and the now-visible board's cards load.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Manual add
\f0\b0  likely recovers via the realtime path 
\f4\i because it flips the branch
\f0\i0 : to add a card you navigate into the board (making it 
\f1\fs26 activeBoard
\f0\fs24 ), and the 
\f1\fs26 createTask
\f0\fs24  insert echoes as a 
\f2\b board-scope change for the now-active board
\f0\b0  \uc0\u8594  
\f1\fs26 boardId === activeBoardIdRef.current
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  
\f1\fs26 reloadOpenBoard()
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  
\f1\fs26 getTasks()
\f0\fs24  \uc0\u8594  all cards reappear. (The new card alone wouldn't do it \'97 
\f1\fs26 createTask
\f0\fs24  only pushes that one task into state; it's the realtime refetch it triggers that reloads the rest.)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 The fix (when you want it)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Every restore path needs a full tasks refetch:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 restoreBoard
\f0\b0\fs24 : add 
\f1\fs26 await refreshTasks()
\f0\fs24  after 
\f1\fs26 loadBoards()
\f0\fs24  \'97 the minimal fix.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Add a context 
\f3\fs26 undeleteBoard
\f0\b0\fs24  (
\f1\fs26 boards.undelete
\f0\fs24  + 
\f1\fs26 loadBoards
\f0\fs24  + 
\f1\fs26 refreshTasks
\f0\fs24 ) and have 
\f2\b Trash
\f0\b0  call it instead of 
\f1\fs26 window.api.boards.undelete
\f0\fs24  directly.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Archive 
\f3\fs26 handleRestore
\f0\b0\fs24 : call the context 
\f1\fs26 restoreBoard
\f0\fs24  instead of hitting 
\f1\fs26 window.api.boards.restore
\f0\fs24  + a local filter, so it goes through the list+tasks refresh (and actually updates the sidebar).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Bundling note: this is the same class of bug as the card-revive issue from the earlier survey \'97 a cloud mutation followed by a partial client refresh. If you fix both together, the shared principle is "any restore/undelete must 
\f1\fs26 refreshTasks()
\f0\fs24  (or 
